{"title_page": "2011 Missouri Valley Conference Baseball Tournament", "text_new": "{{Infobox NCAA Baseball Conference Tournament |\n| Year=2011\n| Conference=Missouri Valley Conference\n| ShortConference=\n| Division=\n| Image=\n| ImageSize=\n| Caption=\n| Teams=8\n| Format=[[Double-elimination]]\n| Ballpark=TD Ameritrade Park\n| City=Omaha, NE\n| Champions={{cbsb link|year=2011|team=Creighton Bluejays|title=Creighton}}\n| TitleCount=2nd\n| Coach=[[Ed Servais]]\n| CoachCount=2nd\n| MVP=Jonas Dufek\n| MVPTeam=[[Creighton Bluejays baseball|Creighton]]\n| Attendance= Total: 37,607<br> Avg: 2,507\n| Television=\n}}\n{{2011 Missouri Valley Conference baseball standings}}\nThe '''2011 [[Missouri Valley Conference Baseball Tournament]]''' took place from May 24\u201328. All eight teams met in the [[double-elimination]] tournament held at [[Creighton Bluejays baseball|Creighton]]'s [[TD Ameritrade Park Omaha]] in [[Omaha, Nebraska]]. Creighton won their second tournament championship and earned the conference's automatic bid to the [[2011 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gocreighton.com/news/2011/5/28/205155860.aspx|title=Baseball Tops Wichita State 3-1 to Win MVC Tournament Title|publisher=Creighton Athletics|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Seeding and format==\nThe league's eight teams were seeded based on conference winning percentage. They then played a two bracket, double-elimination format tournament, with the winner of each bracket then playing a single elimination final.\n{|class=wikitable\n! Team !! W !! L !! PCT !! GB !! Seed\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Creighton || 15 || 6 || .714 ||<center>\u2013</center> ||<center>'''1'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Wichita State || 14 || 7 || .667 ||<center>1</center> ||<center>'''2'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Illinois State || 13 || 8 || .619 ||<center>2</center> ||<center>'''3'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Missouri State || 11 || 9 || .550 ||<center>3.5</center> ||<center>''