second tournament championship and earned the conference's automatic bid to the [[2011 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gocreighton.com/news/2011/5/28/205155860.aspx|title=Baseball Tops Wichita State 3-1 to Win MVC Tournament Title|publisher=Creighton Athletics|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Seeding and format==\nThe league's eight teams were seeded based on conference winning percentage. They then played a two bracket, double-elimination format tournament, with the winner of each bracket then playing a single elimination final.\n{|class=wikitable\n! Team !! W !! L !! PCT !! GB !! Seed\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Creighton || 15 || 6 || .714 ||<center>\u2013</center> ||<center>'''1'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Wichita State || 14 || 7 || .667 ||<center>1</center> ||<center>'''2'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Illinois State || 13 || 8 || .619 ||<center>2</center> ||<center>'''3'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Missouri State || 11 || 9 || .550 ||<center>3.5</center> ||<center>'''4'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Southern Illinois || 11 || 10 || .524 ||<center>4</center> ||<center>'''5'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Indiana State || 8 || 13 || .381 ||<center>6.5</center> ||<center>'''6'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Evansville || 7 || 13 || .350 ||<center>8</center> ||<center>'''7'''</center>\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n| Bradley || 4 || 17 || .190 ||<center>11</center> ||<center>'''8'''</center>\n|}\n\n==Results==\n{{SECBracket\n\n| RD1-seed01=3\n| RD1-team01=Illinois State\n| RD1-score01=2\n| RD1-seed02='''6'''\n| RD1-team02='''Indiana State'''\n| RD1-score02='''5'''\n\n| RD1-seed03='''2'''\n| RD1-team03='''Wichita State'''\n| RD1-score03='''2'''\n| RD1-seed04=7\n| RD1-team04=Evansville\n| RD1-score04=1\n\n| RD1-seed05='''3'''\n| RD1-team05='''Illinois State'''\n| RD1-score05='''4'''*<br>(11)\n| RD1-seed06=7\n| RD1-team06=Evansville\n| RD1-score06=3\n\n| RD1-seed09='''4'''\n| RD1-team09='''Missouri State'''\n| RD1-